10 An Act relating to conventions pursuant to Article V
of the United States Constitution; enacting the Dr.
11 Tom Coburn Act; defining terms; prohibiting certain
conduct; prescribing criminal penalties; providing
12 for noncodification; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
17 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
18 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Dr. Tom Coburn
19 Act".
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 601 of Title 21, unless there is
22 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 As used in this act:
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2299 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. "Commissioner" means a person selected by resolution of the
2 Legislature to represent this state at an Article V convention for
3 proposing amendments;
4 2. "Commission" means the resolution or other measure adopted
5 by the Legislature which sets forth the names of the appointed
6 commissioners, the scope of their authority, and other instructions;
7 and
8 3. "Alternate commissioner" means a person selected to fill a
9 vacancy in the delegation.
10 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 602 of Title 21, unless there is
12 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. A commissioner or alternate commissioner to a convention for
14 proposing amendments held under Article V of the United States
15 Constitution shall not exceed the scope of his or her authority when
16 acting as a commissioner or alternate commissioner. A commissioner
17 or alternate commissioner exceeds the scope of his or her authority
18 by voting or otherwise acting beyond the authority granted in his or
19 her commission, as altered by any duly issued subsequent
20 instructions provided before the vote or other action.
21 B. A commissioner or alternate commissioner who exceeds the
22 scope of his or her authority shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
23 felony.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2299 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 603 of Title 21, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 Any individual who, while not being privileged by law, knowingly
5 bribes, threatens, intimidates, or obstructs a commissioner,
6 alternate commissioner, or a person representing another state in
7 the capacity of a commissioner or alternate commissioner at a
8 convention held in this state, in the performance of his or her
9 duties, or attempts to do so, shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
10 felony.
11 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY
April 21, 2026 - DO PASS
